After some debugging on IRC with @samuncle, it appears mouse wheel scroll events can't be used via the InputMap. It's possible to assign the "Wheel Up Button" and "Wheel Down Button" of a mouse to actions, but they don't seem to be triggered when scrolling the wheel.
On the other hand polling for mouse wheel events works just fine.

**This works:**

```
func _input(event):
    if event.type == InputEvent.MOUSE_BUTTON:
        if event.button_index == BUTTON_WHEEL_UP:
            print("wheel up (event)")
        if event.button_index == BUTTON_WHEEL_DOWN:
            print("wheel down (event)")

func _ready():
    set_process_input(true)
```

**This does not work:**

![script1](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4701338/12302758/2b3337d8-ba27-11e5-871b-a1058bb548a3.png)

```
func _fixed_process(delta):
    if Input.is_action_pressed("wheel_up"):
        print("wheel up (action)")
    if Input.is_action_pressed("wheel_down"):
        print("wheel down (action)")

func _ready():
    set_fixed_process(true)
```

Do we misunderstand the meaning of the "Wheel Up" and "Wheel Down" mouse "buttons" in the InputMap, or are those non-working?

Tested on Linux 64-bit, current master branch.
